Overview

This component creates a form interface for adding new demos to a portfolio or showcase section. It allows users to input details like title, description, URLs (demo and GitHub), and a preview image. The form works only in development mode and includes validation. Once submitted, it saves the demo information and redirects users to the demos page. The interface features a clean, responsive design with dark/light theme support.

The component provides a user-friendly way to manage and add new demo projects to a website's collection, with clear input fields and intuitive navigation controls.

Overview

This component creates a menu management interface where users can add, edit, and delete menu items. It displays a form for inputting item details (name, description, price, and category) and shows all menu items in a list format. Each menu item can be edited or removed, and the interface features a clean, modern design with hover effects and visual feedback for user interactions.

In simple terms, it's like a digital menu board editor that restaurant owners might use to manage their menu items.

Overview

This component creates a form interface for adding new projects to a portfolio. It allows users to input project details including a title, description, image URL, and project URL. The form features a clean, modern design and includes data validation. When submitted, it saves the project details and resets the form, but only functions in development mode. It's essentially a project management tool designed for portfolio administration.

The component provides a user-friendly way to expand a portfolio collection without needing to modify code directly.
